  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Chop the <strong>potatoes </strong>(skins on) into small bite-sized pieces and add them to a baking tray with a drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil </strong>and a pinch of<strong> salt</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and sprinkle over <strong>half</strong> of the <strong>black mustard seeds</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 35 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1617202250120-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1617202250120-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1617202250120-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1617202250120-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1617202250120-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil a kettle</p><p>Add the<strong> eggs</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>(salt prevents the eggs from cracking) and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, cook for exactly 6 min, then fill a bowl of<strong> very cold water</strong> and add the <strong>cooked eggs</strong> to the bowl to cool down quickly</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1617202289549-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1617202289549-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1617202289549-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1617202289549-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1617202289549-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add a sheet of <strong>baking paper</strong> to your chopping board and sprinkle over a light dusting of <strong>flour</strong></p><p>Remove 2<strong> </strong>of the <strong>sausages </strong>from their skins and combine to form a giant meatball, then flatten the meatball into a circle (big enough to coat an egg) onto the floured baking paper</p><p>Repeat this with the <strong>remaining sausages</strong> until you have 2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[4] </span>sausage meat circles</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1617202303646-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1617202303646-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1617202303646-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1617202303646-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1617202303646-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel the <strong>cooled eggs</strong></p><p>Add a <strong>peeled egg</strong> to the centre of each <strong>sausage meat circle</strong></p><p>Wrap the sausage meat around each egg and seal it tightly on all sides so that there aren't any gaps – these are your <strong>sausage-coated eggs</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1617202363026-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1617202363026-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1617202363026-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1617202363026-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1617202363026-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Bash the <strong>crispy onions</strong> with a<strong> rolling pin</strong> until finely crushed and add them to a plate</p><p>Add a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> to a separate plate</p><p>Turn the<strong> sausage-coated eggs</strong> in the <strong>olive oil</strong>, shake off the excess, then add them to the<strong> crushed crispy onions</strong> and press firmly until they're evenly coated all over – these are your<strong> scotch eggs</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1617202376176-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1617202376176-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1617202376176-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1617202376176-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1617202376176-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>scotch eggs </strong>to a<strong> baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray and put the tray in the oven for 15-18 min, or until the sausage is cooked through</p><p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>cornichons</strong> to a <strong>food processor </strong>with the <strong>mustard ketchup</strong>, <strong>cider vinegar</strong> and <strong>remaining black mustard seeds</strong></p><p>Add 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]<strong> </span>olive oil </strong>and pulse until you're left with a chunky texture – this is your<strong> cheat's piccalilli</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
